    <section>
        <title>wrapper.java.command.loglevel</title>
        <para>
            Log level to use when logging the full command line used to launch
            the JVM.  Valid log levels include: <literal moreinfo="none">NONE</literal>
            to never log it.  Or <literal moreinfo="none">FATAL</literal>,
            <literal moreinfo="none">ERROR</literal>, <literal moreinfo="none">STATUS</literal>,
            <literal moreinfo="none">INFO</literal>, or <literal moreinfo="none">DEBUG</literal>,
            to log the command at the specified log level.  The default value is
            <literal moreinfo="none">DEBUG</literal>.
        </para>
        <para>
            Setting the loglevel to <literal moreinfo="none">INFO</literal> for
            example can be a useful way to debug the generated command line without
            having to view all debug output.
        </para>
        <informalexample>
            <simpara><emphasis>Example:</emphasis></simpara>
            <screen format="linespecific"><![CDATA[wrapper.java.command.loglevel=INFO]]></screen>
        </informalexample>
    </section>
